notes.note: Time: TBA First meeting Thursday, August 27, 2:20 - 4:00 pm 328 Plant Science Building Mycorrhizas are mutualistic associations of fungi with roots of plants where fungi depend on plant-assimilated carbon in exchange for improved uptake of mineral nutrients from the soil. Mycorrhizal root colonization is the normal state for most terrestrial plants under most ecological conditions.
